33:11.666 --> 33:13.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the scars that remain today.

33:13.633 --> 33:18.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: On July 23, 1967,
Detroit was hit by a riot.

33:19.833 --> 33:21.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES, Detroit:
Everything broke loose.

33:21.366 --> 33:23.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: Forty-three dead, thousands
injured, and the city in flames.

33:23.933 --> 33:27.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: All we could hear is
fire engines and police sirens.

33:27.300 --> 33:32.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES CRAIG, Detroit Police
Chief: I guess, when I'm being
