And that's certainly true again.

37:11.666 --> 37:14.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: What was
the biggest finding of the
Kerner Commission report?

37:14.333 --> 37:19.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED HARRIS: Our nation is
moving towards two societies,
one white, one black, separate

37:19.933 --> 37:21.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and unequal.

37:21.433 --> 37:24.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: The report
was rejected by the president.

37:24.233 --> 37:26.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
None of its recommendations
were ever adopted.

37:26.333 --> 37:29.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SHEILA COCKREL, Former Detroit
City Councilwoman: The fact that
it never went anywhere, that

37:29.233 --> 37:34.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it really didn't drive the
level of policy and drive the
level of people dealing with

37:36.633 --> 37:41.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
race, is a testament to
how deep-seated and how
tough it is to not only
have the conversations,

37:44.266 --> 37:46.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
but to make the change
that would be required.

37:46.200 --> 37:50.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Sheila Cockrel,
who served on the Detroit
City Council for 15 years,

37:50.700 --> 37:55.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
says white flight already
plaguing Detroit escalated
rapidly after the unrest.

37:57.633 --> 37:59.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Other forces were at play.

37:59.700 --> 38:03.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The auto industry was
hit by an oil crisis
and foreign competition.

38:03.966 --> 38:07.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There were two decades
of government corruption.

38:07.266 --> 38:12.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2008 the global
financial crash hit
Detroit particularly hard.

38:14.200 --> 38:17.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, then, in 2013, Detroit
became the largest municipality
ever to file for bankruptcy.

38:20.400 --> 38:25.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, Detroit police are
adamant that they are trying to
repair their relationship with

38:25.133 --> 38:27.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the public.

38:27.100 --> 38:31.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have trained police
officers in all 12 precincts to
build stronger community ties.

38:32.366 --> 38:33.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Officer Donald Parker.

38:33.566 --> 38:35.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How do you build trust
in a neighborhood?

38:35.866 --> 38:40.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD PARKER, Detroit Police
Department: Building now is us
filtering into the community,

38:40.566 --> 38:44.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
saying hi to Ms. Jones,
and saying, hey, we're
here, we're here, we're
touchable, we're reachable,

38:44.333 --> 38:47.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to let them know not
to be afraid of us.

38:47.866 --> 38:50.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: The composition
of the force has also changed.

38:50.933 --> 38:54.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In 1967, it was 5
percent African-American.

38:54.233 --> 38:59.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, it is about 65 percent
African-American, including
the chief, James Craig.

39:01.233 --> 39:05.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES CRAIG: Well, what happened
50 years ago, I can't say
would never happen in Detroit,

39:06.633 --> 39:08.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
because there's still issues.

39:08.633 --> 39:12.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have one of the highest
poverty rates, and while we have
an above-average relationship

39:12.900 --> 39:16.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with the community, there's
the issue of opportunities.

39:16.933 --> 39:21.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And while that's getting better
and while the city has made
a major turnaround, there's

39:23.966 --> 39:26.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
still this belief that, while
the turnaround is happening
in certain parts of the city,

39:26.900 --> 39:28.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it's not in others.

39:28.900 --> 39:32.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: A sign of
the work remaining to be done:
Detroit's poverty rate is double

39:32.900 --> 39:35.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
what it was in 1967.

39:35.466 --> 39:39.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The city struggles with
segregation, inadequate
housing and has the
lowest school test scores

39:41.466 --> 39:46.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and graduation
rates in the nation.

39:48.400 --> 39:52.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Anika Goss-Foster is with Future
City Detroit, which imagines
modern-day uses for blighted

39:54.566 --> 39:55.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
properties.

39:55.800 --> 39:58.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Goss-Foster's focus
is the next 50 years.

39:58.733 --> 40:02.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANIKA GOSS-FOSTER, Detroit
Future City: We call
them dinosaurs, where
there are old monster

40:02.666 --> 40:07.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
plants that are now sitting
vacant in the middle of
residential neighborhoods.

40:07.066 --> 40:12.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: The old Packard
plant, a dinosaur, abandoned
since the 1990s, is being

40:14.100 --> 40:17.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
developed into the shops
and galleries in hopes of
reviving the neighborhood.

40:17.266 --> 40:20.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANIKA GOSS-FOSTER: Things aren't
happening the way as quickly
as they want it to happen.

40:20.933 --> 40:25.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they certainly aren't
happening at a rate
where it should happen.

40:27.900 --> 40:31.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But if you really pushed,
there are a lot of good things
happening all over the city.

40:31.000 --> 40:35.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are parks that are
being taken care of that have
never been taken care of bore.

40:35.166 --> 40:37.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The city is completely lit.

40:37.500 --> 40:41.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
People are much more involved
in their neighborhoods
than they have ever been.

40:41.800 --> 40:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN:
Entrepreneurs and business
leaders have transformed
7.2 miles of downtown

40:48.800 --> 40:53.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into a booming neighborhood that
has attracted tourists, tech
start-ups and new businesses.

40:55.000 --> 40:58.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the boom hasn't yet trickled
down into the neighborhoods
that Goss-Foster is trying

40:59.400 --> 41:01.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to develop.

41:01.466 --> 41:03.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANIKA GOSS-FOSTER: I think
that there are a lot of black
people that would say they

41:03.066 --> 41:04.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
do feel left out.

41:04.366 --> 41:06.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I wouldn't say that
they feel ignored.

41:06.800 --> 41:10.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I think they feel like,
when is it my turn?

41:10.100 --> 41:12.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Right,
to get investment.

41:12.066 --> 41:15.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANIKA GOSS-FOSTER: To
get the same kind of
attention and investment.

41:15.600 --> 41:19.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Neglect felt
firsthand by Loretta Holmes.

41:19.633 --> 41:21.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES: We
don't have anything.

41:21.400 --> 41:22.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's nothing there anymore.

41:22.866 --> 41:25.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: So, what
happened to the neighborhoods?

41:25.200 --> 41:27.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES:
People moved out.

41:27.300 --> 41:28.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
People moved out.

41:28.300 --> 41:29.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They left.

41:29.366 --> 41:30.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They walked away.

41:30.366 --> 41:32.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
No kept the property up.

41:32.566 --> 41:34.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Loretta
Holmes stayed behind.

41:34.766 --> 41:36.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES: We
were in Central.

41:36.800 --> 41:39.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We were totally a community.

41:39.233 --> 41:40.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We were a community.

41:40.533 --> 41:42.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is what we did.

41:42.166 --> 41:44.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We took care of each other.

41:44.266 --> 41:48.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: She mentors
students at her alma mater,
Detroit's Central High.

41:48.266 --> 41:49.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES: We
give scholarships.

41:49.800 --> 41:53.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We go ahead and we will buy the
jerseys for the football team.

41:53.933 --> 41:58.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kids that doesn't have a
coat, we do it undercover,
because we don't want
the other kids to know.

42:00.900 --> 42:05.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Her investment
in kids is what gives her
hope for a better future for

42:05.233 --> 42:06.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Detroit.

42:06.633 --> 42:09.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is the city of Detroit
better off today than it was?

42:09.133 --> 42:10.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES: Heck no.

42:10.133 --> 42:11.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: In the '60s?

42:11.433 --> 42:13.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES: No.

42:13.366 --> 42:14.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
No.

42:14.366 --> 42:15.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
No, because it's...

42:15.633 --> 42:17.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Better
off than five years ago?

42:17.800 --> 42:20.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LORETTA HOLMES:
Than five years ago?

42:20.400 --> 42:22.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Yes, because now I
can see the change.

42:22.500 --> 42:24.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I really can.

42:24.600 --> 42:28.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Change that,
for a city with a history of
racial conflict and struggle,

42:30.266 --> 42:32.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is long overdue.

42:32.200 --> 42:37.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Soledad O'Brien in Detroit.

42:40.966 --> 42:45.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now we visit
one of the most successful,
prolific women in America,

42:54.900 --> 42:59.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the creative force behind
the Barefoot Contessa
cookbooks and TV shows.

42:59.433 --> 43:03.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
William Brangham recently
went to see Ina Garten at her
home on Long Island, New York,

43:03.333 --> 43:05.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and has this look at
her life and career.

43:05.466 --> 43:07.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Can
I have another bite?

43:07.000 --> 43:08.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
INA GARTEN, Chef: You can
have as much as you like.

43:08.233 --> 43:09.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

43:09.433 --> 43:10.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
This is the best job.

43:10.233 --> 43:11.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

43:11.233 --> 43:12.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
INA GARTEN: Isn't it?

43:12.466 --> 43:13.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is what I get
to do for a living.

43:13.266 --> 43:14.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Isn't it unbelievable?

43:14.500 --> 43:16.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
It's fantastic.

43:16.233 --> 43:19.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Ina Garten is one of the
most famous and beloved
cooks in America today.

43:19.666 --> 43:24.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Better known as the
Barefoot Contessa, she
sits atop a culinary empire
built on her bestselling

43:26.233 --> 43:29.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
cookbooks, with millions
of copies sold, a
string of hit TV shows.

43:29.533 --> 43:32.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
INA GARTEN: Just because it's
a weeknight dinner doesn't
mean it has to be boring.

43:32.466 --> 43:34.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And a
legion of devoted fans.

43:34.933 --> 43:37.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
INA GARTEN: This is my
little secret garden.

43:37.066 --> 43:40.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: We
visited Garten at her
home and headquarters
in East Hampton, New

43:40.466 --> 43:42.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
York.

43:42.633 --> 43:46.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We talked in the huge
barn she had built next
to her House that's now
her office, test kitchen

43:47.333 --> 43:49.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and TV studio, all in one.

43:49.466 --> 43:51.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
INA GARTEN: This is where
the show is shot, and this
is where we test recipes.

43:51.533 --> 43:55.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And every morning, I walk
across the lawn and I meet the
two people, Barbara and Lidey,

43:55.266 --> 43:56.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
who work with me.

43:56.800 --> 43:58.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we just go, OK, what
are we going to do today?

43:58.333 --> 43:59.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That's
the extent of your commute?

43:59.333 --> 44:00.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
INA GARTEN: That's my commute.

44:00.366 --> 44:01.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

44:01.866 --> 44:03.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
INA GARTEN: It's like 100 yards,
I think, maybe less, maybe 50.

44:03.100 --> 44:04.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
Pretty amazing.

44:04.033 --> 44:05.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
INA GARTEN: It's pretty amazing.

44:05.466 --> 44:07.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I usually just put it
right in the middle.

44:07.333 --> 44:09.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Garten's
career began 40 years ago.

44:09.533 --> 44:13.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But, at first, she gave no
hint as to how she'd evolve.

44:13.233 --> 44:18.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the 1970s, newly married to
husband Jeffrey, Garten was a
budget analyst in Washington,

44:18.700 --> 44:20.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
D.C.,

44:20.633 --> 44:22.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
INA GARTEN: I was
working at OMB, Office of
Management and Budget.

44:22.266 --> 44:23.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For
the federal government?

44:23.466 --> 44:25.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
INA GARTEN: Yes,
for Ford and Carter.

44:25.933 --> 44:28.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I worked on
nuclear energy policy.

44:28.033 --> 44:30.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How's that for precedent
for the food business?

44:30.233 --> 44:31.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: It
makes no sense whatsoever.

44:31.400 --> 44:32.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

44:32.400 --> 44:34.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
INA GARTEN: I ran from it.

44:34.400 --> 44:38.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And by the late '70s, I thought,
I have been working here for
four years, and nothing has

44:38.266 --> 44:39.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
happened.

44:39.766 --> 44:42.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I just didn't feel like
I had any impact on anything.

44:42.166 --> 44:45.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I hit 30, and I thought, I
want to do what I want to do.

44:45.700 --> 44:47.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I thought, I want to
be in the food business.

44:47.766 --> 44:51.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: One day, she
saw an ad for a specialty food
store for sale in the Hamptons,

44:51.933 --> 44:54.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the exclusive beach
destination for New Yorkers.

44:54.466 --> 44:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
INA GARTEN: I went home and
I told Jeffrey about it, and
he said, pick something you

44:58.300 --> 44:59.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
love to do.

44:59.833 --> 45:01.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If you love doing it, you
will be really good at it.

45:01.900 --> 45:06.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I made her a very low
offer, the woman who was selling
it, thinking, well, we will

45:06.200 --> 45:07.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
come back.

45:07.200 --> 45:08.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We will negotiate.

45:08.200 --> 45:09.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We drove back to Washington.

45:09.666 --> 45:11.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was in my office the next
day and the phone rang.

45:11.766 --> 45:13.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And she said, thank
you very much.

45:13.333 --> 45:15.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I accept your offer.

45:15.033 --> 45:16.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I just remember going,
oh (EXPLETIVE DELETED).

45:16.400 --> 45:17.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

45:17.866 --> 45:19.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: What
have I gotten myself into?

45:19.433 --> 45:23.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
INA GARTEN: What have I done?

45:23.100 --> 45:24.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM:
And that was it?

45:24.100 --> 45:26.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
INA GARTEN: That was it.

45:26.166 --> 45:28.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
