49:48.633 --> 49:53.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAND Corporation behavioral
scientist Elizabeth
D'Amico offers her
humble opinion on how to

49:53.833 --> 49:55.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
answer their queries.

49:55.866 --> 49:59.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ELIZABETH D'AMICO,
RAND Corporation: Among
family and friends, I'm
regarded as the Dear

50:01.033 --> 50:03.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Abby of adolescent
so-called bad behavior.

50:03.566 --> 50:05.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here's the reason why.

50:05.533 --> 50:09.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because I have researched
alcohol and drug use among teens
for more than 20 years, and

50:09.533 --> 50:14.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I'm a parent, people
always assume I have
devised a foolproof
strategy for talking to

50:14.133 --> 50:16.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
kids about such issues.

50:16.133 --> 50:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lately, I have been fielding
a lot of questions about
marijuana legalization.

50:22.433 --> 50:25.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I do feel like I have an
edge when it comes to talking
to my kids about marijuana.

50:25.733 --> 50:30.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, sometimes, it seems like
I am sharing information on
the fly, as I drive my kids

50:30.500 --> 50:32.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
down a busy L.A.
street to school.

50:32.966 --> 50:37.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Since recreational marijuana
was legalized in California
last fall, a new billboards

50:37.200 --> 50:42.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pop up all the time to advertise
the fine art of smoking
weed and where to buy it.

50:44.233 --> 50:47.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This leads my kids, 11 and
13, to ask a lot of questions:
Why do people smoke marijuana?

50:49.500 --> 50:53.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It can't be bad if
it's legal and they can
advertise, right, mom?

50:53.633 --> 50:58.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
As always, it is best
to give balanced, honest
answers based on facts.

50:58.333 --> 51:00.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Why do people smoke marijuana?

51:00.900 --> 51:04.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some may smoke it for medical
reasons, to help with pain.

51:04.000 --> 51:06.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Others may smoke
it recreationally.

51:06.400 --> 51:08.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Parents might liken
it to alcohol.

51:08.366 --> 51:11.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
You know how some people
have a glass of wine
with dinner to relax?

51:11.500 --> 51:14.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Now some may smoke pot
for the same reason.

51:14.700 --> 51:19.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's also important that
your kids know that getting can
change their mood and behavior.

51:21.600 --> 51:25.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And just like alcohol, tell
your kids it's illegal to drive
after you have smoked pot.

51:27.466 --> 51:30.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I tell my kids the main reason
that marijuana is illegal for
those under 21 is because their

51:30.466 --> 51:35.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
brains are still developing,
and marijuana can affect their
concentration and memory.

51:35.266 --> 51:37.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It may mean you don't
do as well in school.

51:37.766 --> 51:40.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
That can mean fewer
opportunities, like
getting a good job.

51:40.833 --> 51:45.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Given this changing legal
landscape, my kids and yours are
going to be exposed to marijuana

51:45.800 --> 51:48.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
as frequently as
they are to alcohol.

51:48.433 --> 51:53.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now that it's legal, here
come the marketing campaigns,
which all make smoking pot seem

51:53.933 --> 51:56.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
normal.

51:56.033 --> 52:00.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And just like alcohol and
tobacco ads, marijuana ads
may influence their choices.

52:00.933 --> 52:05.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
My own research has shown that
middle school kids who reported
seeing ads for medical marijuana

52:07.366 --> 52:10.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
